National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Secretary General Akiba Takeo of Japan's National Security Secretariat to discuss preparations for President's upcoming trip to South Korea and Japan. They praised Japan's strong response to Russia's invasion of Ukraine, including financial sanctions, export controls, and assistance for Ukraine. They agreed to continue working together on the international response to Russia's aggression. Secretary General Akiba welcomed the President's visit to Tokyo, emphasizing its significance in demonstrating the US commitment to the Indo-Pacific region. They also discussed the importance of the upcoming meeting between the President and Prime Minister Kishida in affirming the strength of the US-Japan alliance, strengthening deterrence in the region, and advancing the shared vision of a free and open Indo-Pacific. Mr. Sullivan emphasized the importance of the second in-person Quad Leaders Meeting in showcasing the Quad's impact on the region.